<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 07 at 3:46PM EDT  by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern
Catoosa, Walker, southwestern Dade and northwestern Chattooga
Counties through 415 PM EDT...
At 345 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was near Sulpher Springs, or 10
miles west of Lafayette, moving south at 10 mph.
HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Lafayette, Trion, Naomi, Center Post, Suttles Mill, Noble, Cloudland
and Cooper Heights.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
